Junk DB

A trivial database to store scripts states


Databases are automatically created when they are first accessed.
A database stores a signle unique state and some generic data.
Data cannot be read back, but only checked for existence, added,
or removed.


protocol:

<db-name> <ACTION> <payload>


actions:

IS,     check if the database unique state equals to the payload

SET,    set the database unique state to the payload

HAS,    check if the database contains the payload

ADD,    add the payload to the database

REM,    remove the payload from the database
